      "comment": "ALDEBARAN ABEL (5) came from one spot wider than this to score a resuming win at Kilmore two runs ago before chasing along the sprint lane for third at his latest appearance at Maryborough, beaten 5.3 metres. Leading hope. KEAYANG TWEETYBIRD (3) is first up for six-and-a-half months but was readied with a nice trial. Draws well and is two for two at this venue so expect a strong return. ALDEBARAN ZANE (9) draws on the back row again but has come from there to win his past two outings at Shepparton so cannot be knocked. BULLAPARK BENO (6) improved last time out to finish runner-up at this venue, his second placing in four starts here since a win at Kilmore.",
